urban sociologist, an
environmental engineer and
playwright Lin-Manuel

52:46.663 --> 52:49.500
Miranda.

52:49.500 --> 52:54.438
In a foundation video, Miranda
spoke of Hamilton, the Broadway
musical he wrote about founding

52:54.438 --> 52:58.442
father Alexander Hamilton
that opened in August.

52:58.442 --> 53:03.881
LIN-MANUEL MIRANDA, Playwright:
I fall in love for a living. I
write musicals, and musicals

53:03.881 --> 53:08.786
take a long time to write. So,
when you have an idea, you
really have to fall in love with

53:08.786 --> 53:14.458
it.

53:14.458 --> 53:21.565
With Hamilton, it's a perfect
marriage of function and form.
Hip-hop is uniquely suited

53:21.565 --> 53:27.838
to tell his story, growing up
orphaned, penniless. Hip-hop has
the energy of revolution. It has

53:27.838 --> 53:32.810
the energy of struggle. It has
the energy that a story like
Hamilton's demands.

53:32.810 --> 53:36.180
This is a story about America
then told by America now.

